Name: Stockholm
Description: The capital region, known for its beautiful archipelago, historic sites, and being the political and cultural center of Sweden.

Name: Vastra Gotaland
Description: Located on the western coast, known for Gothenburg, Sweden s second-largest city, and its maritime culture.

Name: Skane
Description: The southernmost region of Sweden, known for its coastal cities, rural landscapes, and Malmö, one of Sweden s largest cities.

Name: Uppsala
Description: Located just north of Stockholm, known for Uppsala University, the oldest university in Sweden, and its historical significance.

Name: Ostergotland
Description: Located in central Sweden, known for its lush forests, lakes, and the historical city of Linköping.

Name: Jonkoping
Description: Situated in southern Sweden, known for its scenic lakes, particularly Lake Vättern, and its central role in Swedish commerce.

Name: Kronoberg
Description: Located in the southern part of Sweden, known for its forests, lakes, and peaceful rural landscapes.

Name: Kalmar
Description: Located on the southeastern coast, known for its historical landmarks, including Kalmar Castle, and its natural beauty.

Name: Varmland
Description: Located in central Sweden, known for its beautiful forests, lakes, and outdoor recreational activities.

Name: Dalarna
Description: Known for its beautiful natural scenery, the region is also famous for traditional Swedish culture, including the Dala horse.

Name: Gavleborg
Description: Located in central Sweden, known for its forested landscapes, Gävle city, and historic sites.

Name: Vasternorrland
Description: A northern region known for its wilderness, the High Coast, and its rich industrial history.

Name: Jamtland
Description: Located in the central part of Sweden, famous for its mountain landscapes, outdoor activities, and winter sports.

Name: Norrbotten
Description: The northernmost region, known for its Arctic climate, vast wilderness, and the city of Luleå.
